==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deicide
<hw>De"i*cide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>deicida</ets> a deicide (in sense 2); <ets>deus</ets> god +
<ets>c⟦ae⟧dere</ets> to cut, kill: cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧icide</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of killing a
being of a divine nature; particularly, the putting to death of Jesus
Christ.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Earth profaned, yet blessed, with <qex>deicide</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One concerned in putting Christ to death.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deictic</ent>⟦br⟧
